stylometry:
Optimization is one way to perform a quantitative analysis and you want to find the maximum or minimum. 
Objective function: the value to be optimized and it is either the maximum or the minimum
Decision variable: the decision maker can choose what to change and to test different outcomes
Constraints: place restrictions on the values in the changing cells
Feasible region: the set of all feasible solutions
corner points: the very minimum and the very maximum points of a possible solution when graphing
target cell: the cell in excel that contains the objective to be maximized or minimized
changing cells: in excel these are the decision variables
